      <div class="hero-body">
        <h1 class="hero-title">Panax Ginseng</h1>
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">The Mental Stamina Adaptogen</p>
        <p>Panax Ginseng is one of the foundational adaptogens, used in East Asian medicine for over two thousand years and one of the most extensively studied plants in modern cognitive research.</p>
        <p>Its active compounds, called ginsenosides, are a well-characterized family of plant molecules. Modern human trials have studied Panax for sustained mental performance, working memory, and reduced mental fatigue during demanding cognitive work.</p>
      </div>
      <img class="hero-image" src="{{ 'panax-ginseng-hero.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Panax Ginseng, the mental stamina adaptogen" width="1664" height="1034" loading="lazy" />
    </section>

    <section class="mechanism">
      <h2>How Panax Ginseng Works</h2>
      <p class="mechanism-intro">Panax supports the kind of mental energy that builds across a long day. It's the steady one in the stack.</p>
      <div class="mechanism-card">
        <div class="mechanism-points">
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">1.</span>One of the most-studied adaptogens in modern research.</h4><p>Panax Ginseng has been the subject of a large body of peer-reviewed human trials on cognitive performance, mental fatigue, and mood.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">2.</span>Active compounds: ginsenosides.</h4><p>The standardized extract used in research delivers specific levels of ginsenosides, the family of compounds responsible for Panax's cognitive and energy-supporting effects.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">3.</span>Supports cognitive performance under sustained demand.</h4><p>Research suggests Panax helps support working memory and mental accuracy during long stretches of cognitively demanding work.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">4.</span>Supports mental energy without the spike of caffeine.</h4><p>Panax is studied for its role in supporting mental energy and helping reduce mental fatigue through a different pathway than stimulants.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mechanism-footnote">Summarized from published research on Panax Ginseng and cognitive performance.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="split">
      <img class="split-image" src="{{ 'panax-ginseng-cluster.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Panax Ginseng compound detail" width="1466" height="1084" loading="lazy" />
      <div>
        <h2>Why We Use It</h2>
        <p>Panax is the ingredient in DayShift built for sustained cognitive performance. Where caffeine handles acute alertness and Rhodiola handles stress adaptation, Panax supports the steady, long-arc kind of mental energy that holds up across hours of focused work.</p>
        <p>200 mg per packet, standardized for ginsenosides, dosed within the clinically studied range for cognitive performance.</p>
        <div class="focus-block">
          <h3>Key Focus Areas</h3>
          <ul class="focus-list">
            <li>Sustained Energy</li>
            <li>Working Memory</li>
            <li>Mental Stamina</li>
